Many workers will be on furlough this Christmas.With the virus still wreaking havoc and not showing any signs of slowing down, we could have a bad Christmas. Despite Kenya’s lockdown measures, the number of Covid-19 cases continues to rise and challenges arise with the upcoming holiday season. With the virus still wreaking havoc and not showing any signs of slowing down, we could have a bad Christmas. There will be no church gatherings and most retail chains will not have enough goods in stock. This is mainly because of virus-triggered shutdowns that upended supply chains.



