The divine light demands better from us. Retailers are also dealing with their own challenges - the damages sustained by multiple lockdowns. With the rapid downturn suffered by the economy, people suddenly lost all means of income, hence losing the mood to celebrate.
During the Christmas season, Kenyans become party animals; they engage in merry making. While the virus still challenges many, there will always be partying. The rules should ensure the celebrations do not end up in tears.
